==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Traitorous
<hw>Trai"tor*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>tra⟦icir⟧treux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Guilty of treason;
treacherous; perfidious; faithless; <as>as, a <ex>traitorous</ex>
officer or subject</as>.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Consisting in treason; partaking of treason;
implying breach of allegiance; <as>as, a <ex>traitorous</ex>
scheme</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Trai"tor*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Trai"tor*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Traitory</ent>⟦br⟧
